            .</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310217-265-person2376">
                  SARAH 
                  POWELL
               <interp inst="t18310217-265-person2376" type="surname" value="POWELL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-265-person2376" type="given" value="SARAH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-265-person2376" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the wife of Joseph Powell - he lives in Mansell-street, Goodman's-fields; I was in a cart going along <placeName id="t18310217-265-crimeloc1536">Brick-lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18310217-265-crimeloc1536" type="placeName" value="Brick-lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18310217-265-crimeloc1536" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310217-265-off1534 t18310217-265-crimeloc1536"></join>, on the 15th of February, at a quarter before eight o'clock - there was a bag of linen in the cart, which I was bringing from the country to my own house; it contained four sheets and three bags - there was a lad in the cart, but he is not here; a Policeman gave me notice that the property was taken.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. HEATON. Q. Did you see it when you were in Brick-lane? A. No; it was an open cart - it could not have fallen out - I have not promised my witness any thing for her trouble.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310217-265-person2377">
                  CHRISTIANA 
                  THOMPSON
               <interp inst="t18310217-265-person2377" type="surname" value="THOMPSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-265-person2377" type="given" value="CHRISTIANA"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-265-person2377" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was in Brick-lane, and saw Mrs. Powell and a lad in the cart; I saw a man, whom I think was the prisoner, following and watching the cart - he went behind the cart, and took out this bundle; he was running away - I had before seen a Police-constable, and given information; he took the prisoner with the bundle.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. Did he run? A. Yes, when we cried Stop thief! he ran, but not so much as two or three hundred yards; I had not had any thing to drink with the prosecutrix.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310217-265-person2378">
                  GEORGE 
                  BRIDLE
               <interp inst="t18310217-265-person2378" type="surname" value="BRIDLE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-265-person2378" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-265-person2378" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. This young woman pointed out to me a person following the cart; I saw him running from it with the bundle - I ran to take him; he threw down the bundle, and I collared him - I never lost sight of him; it was a quarter before eight o'clock.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. Are you quite sure you saw him with the bundle near the cart? A. Yes; I caught him running - there was no crowd there; it was not dark.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was not near the cart; I crossed to speak to a person, and they ran and took me.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18310217-265-verdict1537" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18310217-265-verdict1537" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. - Aged 19. - <rs id="t18310217-265-punish1538" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18310217-265-punish1538" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310217-265-defend2373 t18310217-265-punish1538"></join>
               Transported for Seven Years
            </rs>.</p>
